goals.question: What is the distribution of flight delays?
goals.rationale: This tells us how many flights were delayed and by how much, which can help us identify patterns and potential causes of delays.

goals.question: What is the average delay time for flights?
goals.visualization: bar chart of delay by origin airport
goals.rationale: This can help us identify which airports have the highest average delay times and potentially investigate why.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight distances?
goals.rationale: This tells us how far most flights travel and can help us identify any outliers or patterns in flight distances.

goals.question: Which airports have the most flights?
goals.visualization: bar chart of flight count by airport
goals.rationale: This can help us identify which airports are the busiest and potentially investigate why.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight dates?
goals.visualization: line chart of flight count by date
goals.rationale: This tells us how many flights occurred on each day and can help us identify any patterns or trends in flight schedules.

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_delay_by_origin = data.groupby('origin')['delay'].mean()
    avg_delay_by_origin.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average delay time for flights?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    flight_counts = data['date'].value_counts().sort_index()
    
    plt.plot(flight_counts.index, flight_counts.values)
    
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight dates?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
